"This one is tricky.. The answer is indeed True. Eating ice cream does not worsens the cold. We may think that ice creams colds the body but it's definitely not so.

There is simply no reason for you to avoid ice cream when you have a cold. By the same token, there is medical evidence to suggest that eating certain foods or modifying your diet while you have a cold can boost your immune system or alter the course of your upper respiratory tract infection.

Thanks for enlightening many with such myth busters.

So the next time u r down with cold, say big yes to ice creams...holaaaaa.

#thefreedomchallenge"
'It is surely false. Eggs are good for heart for unfortunately many think that it is bad. Myth it is.\n\n#thefreedomchallenge'

"False - It's a myth that eggs are bad for your heart
Perfect poached egg
Eggs can form part of a balanced diet, despite their perceived 'bad' reputation due to their cholesterol content. We reveal the secrets of the perfect poached egg.

Eggs do contain some saturated fat, but the butter on your toast or the bacon that may come with your eggs will probably make a more significant contribution to your overall intake.

A boiled, poached or scrambled egg can be a healthy option  just watch out for what you add to them.

Avoid cooking scrambled eggs in butter  use a non-stick pan and add a little unsaturated oil or spread. Swap butter on your toast for unsaturated spread and if you like ketchup with your eggs, remember it's high in sugar and salt."

'Yes ...diabetic people can consume sugar in moderate level...have tried this personally. Earlier, people with diabetes were told to completely avoid sugar. Many thought that eating sugar would raise blood glucose levels very high.

But Research around this issue has shown that while the type of carbohydrate can affect how quickly blood glucose levels rise, the total amount of carbohydrate you eat affects blood glucose levels more than the type. Now experts agree that you can substitute small amounts of sugar for other carbohydrate containing foods into your meal plan and still keep your blood glucose levels on track.

#thefreedomchallenge'

'True -  sugar does not raise blood sugar levels any more than starches do. This means you can eat sugary foods (cookies, cakes, pies, and candy) as long as you count them as part of your total carbohydrate intake. Keep in mind that foods high in sugar are often high in fat and calories, and if eaten in excess might elevate sugar and triglyceride levels, and can lead to weight gain.'
'True in measured amounts per day quota'

'Sharing one of the experience today in your clinic-

So the receptionist called Dr. Merina for oral consultation but didnt help as issue appeared bit critical. It seemed that doctor Sandesh denied to look at my son upon requesting by Dr. Merina. Finally Dr. Merina had to travel again to clinic and she satisfactorily resolved my issue. I am thankful to her.
I finally want to raise a question here- Is it that the clinics are set up mere as a business?? With no logic being applied and a doctor denying to look at the patient without being paid separately, though i paid consultation just 3 hours back for same issue???'

"I am a happy patient of Indraprastha Apollo Hospital, Delhi. I was of the opinion that Apollo Hospitals is one of the best in country. Today, I visited Apollo Noida for the first time for some emergency treatment and to my shock, I found, it is not that great. The emergency ward was full of mosquitoes, beds were not clean, I even spotted a dirty bedsheet on the bed given to me though when I complained about it, the nurse asked me to change the bed. I complained about the mosquitoes and heard other patients complaining about the same. The staff then called a housekeeping boy who tried to kill off the mosquitoes with a mosquito racket. I was surprised to see their casual response to this serious matter. The nurse who attended me was quite rude when I complained about the unusual pain I felt in my cannula. I wonder how can there be so much difference in the services of two branches of such renowned hospital. I have the option of choosing another hospital for the next time but I don't want to ignore this. I will be really grateful if the concerned people can look into the matter and address my complaint."

'#ThingsMomsDo #PowerMom #MothersDay #Powerhouse Mother\'s are created in the image of God . On this International Mother\'s day I salute the very spirit of motherhood which makes all the mother\'s so very unique, strong and warm. My Mom #ShantiJoshi is truly special to me and what ever I am today, is all because of my mom . Like all mothers ,one thing which puts her on the highest platform is her SELFLESSNESS . She loves to take the backseat and inspire us to shine like bright stars. It\'s never "I" for her , it\'s always her children . She is a teacher, always shaping the young minds who will be the citizens of tomorrow. She is humble, calm, always ready to help others. Currently she is giving free tutions to needy kids ( Kids of servants, guard, drivers of our society) and also provide them free stationary and other stuff on regular basis. For me she is my super mom because she taught me the greatest lesson in life, that is, when life seems like its not worth living, never give up, no matter how hard or how rough it is, it will always get better. I lost my Dad during my final year law exams. I had my last paper 4 days after the day we lost Papa. I was too attached to Papa and was too too sad and did not wish to take the exam since I could not focus on studying and was only thinking why Papa had to leave us so early.My Mom stood up for me and my siblings like a pillar of strength though she was the one whose loss was the biggest, her life partner.\nShe came to me one day before the exam and just said one sentence, "Your father wanted you to be a lawyer, study to fulfill his wish." And I understood.\nI studied, appeared for the exam and because of my Mom I could fulfill my dads wish! She is the strongest woman I have known. I am proud of My Mom. Everyone knows that I am her Son, But only I know that she is my Sun, lightening my life with her hugs and love. Thanks for everything Mom. Happy Mothers Day.'

"I still remember my stressful shift job in a call center during my initial years of career.

It was typically a 9 hour shift which ends at 3.30 or 4.00 am in the morning. Waiting for a company transport shuttle and then getting the right one, sleep deprived, I come home, ring the bell hoping someone would wake up and open the door.

And no matter who opens the door. I see my mother waking up from sleep. Seeing my hungry face, immediately runs into kitchen to make either maggi or garam garam dosa ready for me to eat.

I don't know if its a sweetest thing or not but I never wanted to give her that trouble then but you know, they never listen.

I sometimes feel that I'm glad I stay with my mother and wish her directly if its her Birthday, instead of calling her to wish from some other city unlike my other colleagues. Oh well !"

"#MothersDay A mother's love is beyond comparison and Mother's day is the perfect day to dedicate sheer of love and affection to her. My mother-in-law, Chanda Devi Dalmiya is the most important person in my life as she has given me her wonderful son. Her personality, her nature, thoughts and the way of nurturing kids with love and care inspires me. She is spiritual, she is a diva and the most special person in my life. She held my hands the day I came to my husband's home and since then she always stands by me and I can say she is the strongest influence. This Mother's Day I honor my mother by gifting her beautiful photo collage, wonderful saree and chocolates. I love you mom for you have been my truest friend when trials heavy and sudden fell upon me, when adversity took the place of prosperity and when my own relatives went hostile for some time. Whenever the trouble thickens around me, she always clings to me and endeavors by her kind precepts and counsels to dissipate the clouds of darkness and cause peace to return to my heart. My friend, philosopher and guide, my teacher my mom..This post is dedicated to you and I pray to God that everyone gets a loving, caring and energetic mother in law like you. A home without you is like a ship without a radar,.truly! May you live for hundred more years to come.Love u maa.."

'#CloseToMyHeart #contest.\nOver the course of our life, we meet many people with whom we form many relations. There are some of them that are inevitable like our parents, siblings, there are some we consciously form like friends, clients, colleagues etc. and then there are some which are both and yet neither. My relationship with my husband Vipin is of this category. It was inevitable that we met; we were always drifting towards each other unconscious of our affinity. It was inevitable that we fought when we first met (We could never ignore each other). It was inevitable that we became friends post that, we were always missing each other and always craving for that best friend that we found in each other. We were in the same office and same team (our first job at a software giant in 2011). One day when we left office together for home, it started raining heavily (our first rains) and my sandal broke, I was a mess and embarrassed to the core with passing people staring at me. He just looked at me, removed his shoes and said, Lets walk barefoot till our vehicle, its so much fun to walk barefoot on grass in rains and so we walked barefoot in the rains that day, seeing us few others also joined and I had so much fun in the rain that day. I guess I made up my mind to marry him that day, a guy who could so easily turn my embarrassment and discomfort into so much fun was the one for me. Over the past few years we have become each others life. He cares for me like the worried parents yet not treating me like a kid, he protects me like an elder brother yet not treating me like an errant teenager, he is my best friend, my trusted advisor, my nurse when I am sick and a lover who makes me feel complete, my real diamond. Today, we have known each other for 5 years and married for 3 years. With him in my life, I feel complete. Apollo Hospitals'

-Psychogenic cough
-Lung cancer

"The American Academy of Pediatrics recommends exclusive breast-feeding for the first six months after birth  and breast-feeding in combination with solids foods until at least age 1. Extended breast-feeding is recommended as long as you and your baby wish to continue. Still, when to start weaning your child is a personal decision.

It's often easiest to begin weaning when your baby starts the process  which might be sooner or later than you expect. Changes in breast-feeding patterns leading to weaning often begin naturally at age 6 months, when solid foods are typically introduced. Some children begin to seek other forms of nutrition and comfort at around age 1. By this age, children typically eat a variety of solid foods and might be able to drink from a cup. Other children might not initiate weaning until they become toddlers, when they're less willing to sit still during breast-feeding.

You might also decide when to start the weaning process yourself. This might be more difficult than following your child's lead  but can be done with some extra care and sensitivity."
